    "creation_date" : 1759464432,
    "answer_id" : 79781430,
    "question_id" : 62800489,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<h2>Modern Java</h2>\n<p>Easier work now in modern Java.</p>\n<h3>Record</h3>\n<p>In Java 16+, use the <a href=\"https://openjdk.org/jeps/395\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">records</a> feature to neatly define your own class whose main purpose is to transparently communicate shallowly-immutable data.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>store pairs of names and addresses in a collection</p>\n</blockquote>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>record NameAddress ( String name , String address ) {}\n</code></pre>\n<h3><code>SequencedCollection</code> &amp; <code>List.of</code></h3>\n<p>Populate a <a href=\"https://openjdk.org/jeps/431\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">sequenced collection</a> of such objects in Java 21+.</p>\n<p>Use literal fashion with <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/25/docs/api/java.base/java/util/List.html#of(E,E,E,E)\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>List.of</code></a> of Java 9+.</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>SequencedCollection &lt; NameAddress &gt; nameAddresses =\n    List.of(\n        new NameAddress( &quot;Alice&quot; , &quot;101 Main ST&quot; ) ,\n        new NameAddress( &quot;Bob&quot; , &quot;202 Oak Ave&quot;) ,\n        new NameAddress( &quot;Carol&quot; , &quot;303 Coconut Drive&quot; ) \n    );\n</code></pre>\n<p>For a modifiable collection, pass the unmodifiable list returned by <code>List.of</code> to the constructor of another class such as <code>ArrayList</code>.</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>SequencedCollection &lt; NameAddress &gt; nameAddresses =\n    new ArrayList&lt;&gt;(\n        List.of(\n            new NameAddress( &quot;Alice&quot; , &quot;101 Main ST&quot; ) ,\n            new NameAddress( &quot;Bob&quot; , &quot;202 Oak Ave&quot;) ,\n            new NameAddress( &quot;Carol&quot; , &quot;303 Coconut Drive&quot; ) \n        )\n    );\n</code></pre>\n<h3><code>IO.println</code></h3>\n<p>Dump to console using <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/25/docs/api/java.base/java/lang/IO.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">IO</a>. (Before Java 25, use <code>System.out</code>.)</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>nameAddresses.forEach( IO :: println );\n</code></pre>\n<hr />\n<p>See details in a longer <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/a/79781428/642706\">Answer of mine</a> on a similar Question.</p>\n"
  } ],
